description: It's the return of Riot, the super-villain who can multiply himself over and over again (he's his own fan club)! In this special issue, Superman puts an end to the villain's career...permanently!
name: Riot Runs Rampant!

description: Stephanie Brown goes into labour so Robin asks Flash to take him to Gotham heights, only now Robin has to explain to his father what he's doing out there after going missing for 48 hours.
name: A Blessed Event

description:
While battling the Soldiers of the Serpent, will Thunderstrike choose to fulfill his duty to the new Avengers or to his deceased father? Meanwhile, the next generation of the Earth¹s Mightiest Heroes have finally uncovered the menace that broke the spirit of their predecessors, and now must decide how to deal with it! And, as if that wasn't enough, we introduce an all-new hero: the beautiful and powerful Blacklight!

Homage cover to Avengers vol.1 number 73.
name: Team Matters

description:
The Juggernaut continues to crash from dimension to dimension...but how can the X-Men stop the unstoppable?

Today for the X-Men the term that would be best to describe their location would be "Lost in space" but for the X-Men they're half a Universe away, in time, the X-Men realize that they were called by the mysterious creature Ejulp to help stop the rampaging Juggernaut on one of his rages as he managed to get himself into the damaged dimension, little does he know the longer his rampage goes the more damaged the dimension gets, Professor X and the rest of the X-Men do their best, with Wolverine and Charles snapping Cain down, Kitty Pryde, Colossus, Night-crawler and Gambit figuring out how to get themselves out of the dimension before it's too late and Storm finding out what's behind all this, but the answer and the conclusion may shock her and the X-Men more than they expected.
name: Unstoppable!

description:
After somehow making his way back into the heavily guarded New York City from Citrusville, Florida, Havok is having a hard time now getting out of the city to meet up with Elektra and Scotty again. He's on the phone with Elektra when someone arrives at the X-Mansion and the line goes dead. In a panic, he starts to run down the street, and when he breaks a mutant check point, he is pursued into an alley by Sentinels. He's about to melt them when they seem to sink into the concrete below them. The ground opens up underneath him and he falls into a cavern where he awakens to meet Ben Grimm, the Mole Man, and Callisto, (along with some Morlocks and moloids). They talk to him about how they've been getting people out of the city through their tunnels, and they're not 100% sure they can trust him since it's his wife who is trying to take over the world.

In Washington, D.C., The Goblin Queen is yelling at President Reed Richards because he almost let 'him' know about their plans. ('Him' is unrevealed). Bloodstorm shows up and tells the Queen that Havok is back in New York, so they all take off back there to find him.

Ben eventually agrees to show Havok a way out of the city, and when they get out, the entire evil Six is there waiting for them with Sentinels. Apparently, Callisto told the Queen where Havok would be on the condition that the Queen left the Morlocks and Moloids alone. The Queen tries to convince Havok to join her again and bring Scotty with him, and when he declines, yet again, she barbecues Callisto's face, and they all start to fight. Havok takes out Iceman, Ben is tied up with The Brute, and Bloodstorm changes into a wolf and attacks Havok. He throws her at The Fallen with his power, and right as he's getting up, the Queen takes aim at his head. He's upon death when the Mole Man's Mole monster pushes up underneath them, in an effort to rescue Callisto. Just as The Queen decides to unleash the Sentinels, they explode into all of their tiny pieces as Magneto comes onto the scene.
name: The Uncanny

description: OverviewTarzan encounters the embattled castle of Abner Perry, the scientist whose original mole machine first brought civilization to the hidden world. But civilization is exactly what Tarzan doesn't want, especially when he sees how it has turned the Pellucidarians into lazy, fat slobs. When Tarzan frees one of Perry's prisoners, he once again leaves civilization, but this time, civilization follows him . . . in the form of an angry army!

name: Big Julie, the Gangster Gorilla / daddy's little girl / J2's Funny Fairy Tales for Fools & Felons: Jack and the Big Score

description: Burning in Effigy: Part 1 of 2. Guest-starring Jade. Kyle goes up against a deadly new villain whose fiery powers rival his own.
name: Burning In Effigy! 1 of 2

description:
The issue opens with a future version of Hourman fighting the Lord of Time over the Timepoint. They fight across time and space, but at one point the Timepoint begins to vanish. Future Hourman recognizes that the Lord of Time has done something to affect his own past, so future Hourman travels back along his own timestream to find out what.
 
In Happy Harbor, Snapper Carr and Bethany Lee help Hourman order his first cup of cappuccino. In reward for helping him out, Hourman brings Snapper and Bethany to his Timeship. Bethany tries her hands at steering, and brings them outside the timestream (aka Hypertime). There, they meet an alternate version of Snapper Carr and give him a ride to the Amazon/ Gorilla City War. As our Snapper asks Hourman about what Hypertime is, they are attacked by the Lord of Time.
 
The Lord of Time sends Hourman, Snapper, and Bethany to Dallas on November 22, 1963. They find, though, that everything is black-and-white and that there are aliens present. The three are confronted by a former hero calling himself the Catastronaut. The trio realizes this point in history is actually a prison used by the Lord of Time, and none of them can do anything to affect the actual timestream.
 
Hourman tries to break free by breaking through the temporal blockade, but fails and comes crashing back to Earth. With Hourman’s powers used up, the three find themselves trapped.
name: Timepoint

deck: Supergirl battles Murmur. Cassandra (of Greek myth), whom she met previously during the Millennium Giants crisis, pays her a visit.
description: Just as Linda is about to get her art displayed in a Paris gallery, a new super-powered creep comes to beat her up.
name: Above A Murmur

description: Ekimus wants to free Alex, but first he must face Saint George, one of the most feared foes of all vampires. Meanwhile, Scarlett, against all her beliefs, must make a decision that will change her life forever. Also, an unholy alliance is made as judgment day comes to all the creatures of the night in New York. If you're a Big Apple vampire, you can run but you can't hide!
name: Lamentum

description:
An ongoing horror anthology, featuring Jim Lee's first story art for a DC title. Three tales of modern horror for the new millennium, including "The Rocketman" (written by Richard Bruning, with art by Jim Lee), "Wolf Girl Eats" (written by Bruce Jones, with art by Richard Corben), and "Nice Neighborhood" (written by Jen Van Meter, with art by Frank Quitely).

Notes:

  • Ranked #47 in Wizard Magazine's list of "100 Best Single Issue Comics Since You Were Born".
  • Three short stories, told by three different teams of writers and artist.
  • Jim Lee's first story art for a DC title.
name: Rocket-Man / Nice Neighborhood / Wolf Girl Eats

concept_credits.name: 100 Best Single Issue Comics Since You Were Born

first_appearance_concepts.name: 100 Best Single Issue Comics Since You Were Born

description: "Millennium Meteor" part 1! Mitch escapes The Lab with the help of his new friends the Forgotten Heroes, who believe him to be their long-lost leader, the Immortal Man. Is Mitch the man they have been looking for? And what does the Immortal Man's greatest foe--Vandal Savage--plan to do if he is?
name: Millennium Then

description: Etrigan returns to face his nemesis Axilano.
name: Magic is Everywhere

description:
Overview

Following an encounter with a figure from his past, Angel must now face a horror that he had thought long destroyed. The monster, however, could hold the key to Angel's salvation . . . or his destruction! Jumping from the pages of Buffy the Vampire Slayer comes the heroic, tortured vampire Angel in his own three-issue series!
name: The Hollower, Part 2

description: Buffy the next runway supermodel? Believe it! Buffy pursues a potential modeling career only to learn that beauty isn't only skin deep. Meanwhile, with Selke regaining her strength, she decides to pay a visit to the local vampire coven... with mixed results. All the action and drama of the weekly television series captured in a monthly comic book!
name: Hey, Good Lookin' Part 2

description:
The JLA confronts the Martian Manhunter regarding his apparent attack on several of his teammates.

When J'onn is brought into the Watchtower to answer for his troubling conduct, he is compliant and peaceful. But when his evil twin brother Ma'alefa'ak attacks his friends while remaining invisible and intangible, J'onn is forced to take desperate measures to prevent the murder of the Justice League.
name: My Brother's Keeper

description: As Dick Grayson started his first week at the Police academy, a new acrobatic team began looting the looters - Double Dare.
name: Double Dare

description:
The idea of the Bat itself has been around for thousands of years and it all began with Nekhrun.

Then

14,000 years ago a plot to over throw Osiris began. Set the evil God wants the world to himself and the bride of Osiris as a trophy along with the Rod of Light which holds the secretes of universe.

Now

In the world that is Batman(Bruce Wayne) he along with Sheila Ramsey set forth to uncover the secrets about the death of Set and the hidden truth of who truly did slay the beast of a man, and to show the world that the Bat God known as Nekhrun cannot be erased from history and the books.
name: Batman: Book of the Dead - Book 1 of 2

description: Aquaman, Big Barda, Deadman, Guy Gardner, Impulse, Plastic Man and Zatanna each team up with Green Lantern in their own unique short stories.
name: Phases; Art Attack; Fallen Idols; Everybody Goes to Guys; The Lantern's Apprentice; Anything You Can Do; Crosscut

description: It's the return of Mastermind, the Perfessor and Mister Nice (from the pages of the original BATMAN ADVENTURES series)! This criminal trio has faced its share of challenges in the past, but now a visit from a strange child could lead to the dissolution of their partnership, if not their very lives! Can Batman save some of his greatest enemies?
name: The End

description:
Jailbreak in Shadow City! Featuring: Lockdown and Rosetta Stone.

The Fantastic Four are trapped... in someone else's video game? At least that's Reed's theory as he discovers the denizens of Shadow City are actually in stasis.
name: Bedlam breakout

description: They wanted technology...but not like this! The Team of Six must avoid becoming tonight's Tandoori special and somehow disable..."The Stove"!
name: The Stove!

description:
In the previous issue, Spider-man had tracked the masked menace known as Mysterio, to the Osborn Studios. And things had gone wrong for him. Mysterio had given him the slip and managed to change into superhero mode.

Now Spider-man is trapped in a virtual reality room, his Spider-sense going berserk and him being continuously clobbered by Mysterio. But suddenly, Peter gets an idea. His spider-sense is being triggered by the spider-tracer he planted on Mysterio. He punches in the opposite direction of the illusion of Mysterio and hits the real Mysterio. But Mysterio is not outdone. He tells Spider-man that he has framed him for all the crimes he has committed himself. Then he pours a gas and starts to disappear. But Spider-man is ready for him. He smashes Mysterio's visor and reveals him as Quintin Beck. Spider-man had turned on the intercom in the room, so all of his conversation with Mysterio has been recorded. Norman Osborn comes and greets Spider-man, saying that he offers him the chance to act in a movie.

Peter comes back to J.Jonah Jameson, without photos as usual, and tells him that this new proposition for Spider-man could turn out to be a big photo opportunity for the Daily Bugle. Jameson agrees to send him to the shooting place. He goes back to Aunt May and tells her about his plans. May tells him to be careful.

Spider-man goes with the crew to a desert for the shoot. The crew tell him to run around for them to use special effects. Spider-man suddenly senses danger. He finds himself face to face with the Green Goblin. Spider-man is at a real disadvantage without any place to swing, and so he is suddenly an easy target for the Goblin. Spider-man finds out a cave and goes inside, hoping to escape the Goblin. Goblin comes inside and is attacked by Spider-man. But he manages to throw a smoke bomb and fill the cave with smoke.

Spider-man can sense danger. When the smoke clears, he sees himself facing the Hulk. The Hulk starts smashing, telling Spider-man that he can never be caught. Spider-man somehow manages to dodge his attacks and keep himself on his feet. He punches Hulk once but bruises his knuckles. The Goblin is watching from the sidelines, hoping to observe his enemy's weakness. Spider-man tries a desperate gamble. He makes the Hulk smash a rock-pillar. The whole cave comes down on Hulk's head, but Spider-man manages to get free.

But Spider-man is still not out of danger. The Green Goblin renews his attack on Spider-man. Spider-man manages to latch onto his glider but Goblin turns his webbing into the exhaust gas, burning it and dropping Spider-man into a pond. But suddenly, the Hulk makes his way out of the debris. Green goblin weighs his options and leaves the scene. The Hulk, too waits for a while, but jumps away after seeing a military helicopter.

Spider-man goes back to Norman Osborn, asking for his half a million dollars. He returns empty-handed when Norman shows him the documents telling that Spider-man would get his money only when the film was complete.

Norman Osborn returns to his work in his secret Goblin laboratory. He knows that he must become more powerful in order to defeat Spider-man.

The main character, Al Bizarro, is a clone of a former LexCorp employee named Al Beezer. Created as a test for Dr. Happersen's cloning equipment which eventually created a Post-Crisis Bizarro, he was placed in suspended animation and forgotten.

When he is freed, he begins a search for his own identity, and his purpose in life, which eventually takes him to Apokolips (where he befriends a Female Fury named Seera), and later to South America.

In a parody of the original Bizarro code, Al Beezer tells Al Bizarro that, if he wants to be happy, he should do "the exact opposite" of everything the original Al did.
name: Vivisimilitude

description:
Awaking in the Aquacave with no powers, Aquaman must use his agility and strength to battle Charybdis.

Aquaman the awakens restrained in the cave to see Charybdis return with Mera, Dolphin, and Garth as his newest captives. Aquaman then uses his hand to free himself of his chains and attacks but is caught by surprise when he learns he has captured his mother, and begins beating him until Mera uses her hardwater powers to knock him away from Aquaman. Aquaman then lures him out to the open ocean using his speed to avoid his attacks, forcing Charybdis to use the telepathy however the fish refuses his order.

Aquaman then leads him toward Noble's city where several citizens slow him down while he uses the tunnels to travel thousands of miles away with Charybdis following. While Mera frees all of the prisoners in the aquacave. Aquaman then overcomes and prepares to stab his foe, but hesitates momentarily as he uses Atlan's powers to teleport them both away ending up in the domain of the Fire Trolls.
name: Piranha-Man Bites

description: In this issue, the Green Lantern and Captain Marvel continue to explore the 5th Dimension to look for a way to stop the rampaging Djinn. On Earth the JSA and JLA try to keep everything from going to Hell, while Batman and Aquaman fight Triumph and Gypsy in The Tower.
name: Crisis Times Five! Part Four: Gods & Monsters

description: In response to popular demand, multiple Eisner Award winner Stan Sakai presents Usagi in another "Inspector Ishida mystery"! In this issue, Ishida teams up with the rabbit ronin to investigate the disappearance of men from the lower levels of society. The inquiry leads them to a grisly, black market for fresh corpses used in a ritual hundreds of years old.
name: Taméshigiri

description:
"No Man's Land" part 19 and "Mark of Cain" part 1! One of the world's deadliest assassins has been dispatched to No Man's Land to kill one of its denizens. And the only person that stands in his way is a mysterious, seemingly mute young female agent of Oracle, one who may have ties to the assassin himself. Featuring the first appearance of Cassandra Cain! Continued in DETECTIVE COMICS (1937-2011) #734.

Batgirl has failed Batman, and people under her protection have been killed by Two-Face. Meanwhile, Barbara Gordon has a new helper who turns out to be the daughter of the mercenary Cain, preventing her father from killing James Gordon.
name: Mark of Cain Part 1

description: Claim Jumping part 1 of 2. Gotham City is an official No Man's Land, divided into territories controlled by various factions. Two-Face decides to change those territories.
name: Claim Jumping

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description: The crews ship is discovered and Akiko has to pretend to be an alien, of all things!, to ensure its safety.

Robin's dad, Jack Drake decides to move back to Gotham Heights, much to Robin's relief. Three of Nick Scratch's goons have held a hospital hostage as one needs medical attention. Things go more awry when they 'devils' discover their odd physiology.
name: Gomers

description: Captain America guest-stars in chapter one of a major two-part story that¹s been building since issue six! Having finally uncovered the menace that broke the spirit of their predecessors, the next generation of the Earth¹s Mightiest Heroes travel into a twisted reality where they are forced to battle demented versions of the original Avengers! Meet the dreaded Thunder Guard - Donar, Iron Cross, Pincer, the Mster, Deadeye, Storm Trooper and more! Plus: our heroes finally meet and learn the terrible fate of Captain America!
name: Ragnarok!

description:
Spider-Girl is stopping a carjacking by Charlie and his gang, as her father, the former Spider-Man watches on. She easily dispatches three of them, and her father interferes with the last, much to her anger. He still does not trust her in handling them all, and She is apprehensive about it.

At school, Brad, Davida, and Courtney are concerned for Brad after he beast Moose, and they want May to talk to him, as he likes her. She agrees, and as she goes to talk to him, Moose and Brad almost get in a fight and Courtney stops Moose, who seems to like her.

On her free lunch hour, Spider-Girl spots Psi-Lord of the Fantastic Five and goes to talk to him. He tells her that Spyral is back loose, and that she should stay away from him. She is offended, and takes it upon herself to find him. Spotting him near an exploding warehouse, she tackles him into some dimensional portal, transporting him and her into another time.

She arrives in her father's time, and even watches as Spider-Man, her father, gives her a tour of the school. She encounters Liz Allen, who is jealous of her, Flash Thompson, who she doesn't like, and others. After parting ways with him, she follows him and he attacks her because he thinks she is a poser. When a woman is being robbed, Spider-Man aids her while Mayday flees.

May sleeps in the girls locker room of Midtown High, and wakes up. She visits Aunt May, saying she wants to visit with Peter. Her and May have a nice discussion, and Mayday just wanted to see her. She encourages her to set Peter up with Mary Jane.

Mayday leaves and is assaulted by the Spider-Slayer, as J. Jonah Jameson thinks she is Spider-Man.
name: Father's Day

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: OverviewTarzan has alienated himself from the surface world, become a fugitive wanted for murder. He's alienated himself from the human and semi-human tribes of Pellucidar, become a social outcast and a traitor. What is there left for him to do, but wander into the vast, unknown wilderness at the Earth's core, into the realm of legend.

name: On the Road with Wolverine / J2's Funny Fairy Tales for Fools & Felons: a Cantankerous Juggie in King Arthur's Court

description: The fiery new villain Effigy is giving Green Lantern all he can handle. As the battle escalates, Kyle may make a decision that could cost both combatants dearly.
name: [Burning In Effigy! 2 of 2: Angry Youth]

description:
Continued from last issue. Hourman, Snapper Carr, and Bethany Lee are trapped in the Lord of Time’s 1963 frozen point in time, aka the Timepoint. Hourman explodes, and the future version of Hourman from last issue appears. Future Hourman has tracked down the Lord of Time, but is now trapped as well. Future Hourman hugs Snapper, and passionately kisses Bethany. He rebuilds our Hourman, and the two try to figure out a way to escape the time prison.
 
The two Hourmen rebuild the Timeship, and use it to try to break through the temporal blockade. However, outside the Timepoint, the Lord of Time as now absorbed the Timepoint into his armor, providing additional defenses. These additional defenses manifest as globular “antibodies” that attack the Timeship.
 
Meanwhile, still in the Timepoint, Snapper and Bethany discuss their situation. The two Hourmen return from their attempt unsuccessful. However, Snapper gives them an idea when he accuses future Hoiurman of “making time” with Bethany. The Hourmen age Snapper to an old man, which destabilizes the Timepoint, allowing them to break free.
 
The four of them find themselves pouring out of the Lord of Time’s armor. The Lord of Time uses Brainiac 64’s chronostop to freeze everyone, but our Hourman breaks free. He de-ages the Lord of Time to an infant.
 
Our Hourman takes the Timepoint, while future Hourman takes the infant Lord of Time. Hourman returns Snapper to his rightful age. Future Hourman says goodbye to Snapper and Bethany, mysteriously mentioning to Bethany that “the policeman won’t really love you.” Future Hourman sends our trio back to Earth, where they find themselves at the Tyler ancestral manor. At the manor, Snapper finds a pill of Miraclo, and prompts Hourman to take it.
name: Hourmen

deck: Supergirl battle Parasite in Paris. Young Justice appearance. Part 1 of 2.
description: Linda's Paris debut is complicated by a speaking engagement back home at the same time, and an interruption by Parasite.
name: We'll Always Have Parasite

description: Includes an original Books of Faerie back-up feature entitled "The Scrying Pool".
name: Wrong Side of the Tracks

description: This horror anthology offers three offbeat horror stories to darken your summer days, VERTIGO-style. A silent child discovers a microscopic world that others don't want her to see in "Maggie and Her Microscope" (written by Dean Motter with art by Bill Sienkiewicz); a pair of feds on surveillance play a sordid game of psychological chess in "Food Chain" (written by Brian Azzarello with art by Eduardo Risso); and a young woman discovers a ghastly photograph on a street corner, only to discover that it's the first piece to an even more gruesome puzzle, in "Found Object" (written by Bob Fingerman with art by Pat McKeown).
name: Maggie and Her Microscope; Found Object; Food Chain

description: Terry must face an ancient mummy that attemts to kidnapp Dana.
name: Mummy Oh! and Juliet!

description:
Overview

It all comes down to this, sports fans! In the ring to my left: the Hollower--vampire's only natural predator other than the Slayer! And in the ring to my right: Angel--champion of the undead, ex-boyfriend of the Slayer, and one all-around bad mother! Place your bets now, 'cause this one's gonna get nasty! From the pages of the monthly hit, Buffy the Vampire Slayer, comes Angel--vampire hero and hunky heartthrob.
name: The Hollower, Part 3

description:
While the JLA investigates the Martian Manhunter's seeming death on the moon, J'onn slowly recovers on Earth. Appearances by Superman, Wonder Woman, Aquaman, Steel, Huntress, Big Barda, Plastic Man, Flash, and Orion.

With J'onn out of the picture, Malefic decides the Justice League must follow suit. J'onn literally reforms himself after faking his death, while recounting the time when he defended his brother before the Father of the Elders. Absorbing mass from the Earth, J'onn prepares to bring Malefic to justice.
name: Abandon All Hope

description: Nightwing learned the identity of Double Dare through his circus connections. He and the sisters were caught by 3 of Blockbuster's goons: Stallion, Brutale, and the Electrocutioner.
name: Acts of Violence
Batman: Book of the Dead - Book 2 of 2

description: A seemingly reformed Harley Quinn has written a romance novel. But bad sales and a savaging by the critics (not to mention her deep-running criminal streak) send her on a rampage that involves mind-control and mindless destruction.
name: Masks of Love: A Harley Quinn Romance

description:
Overview

The Fantastic Four arrive on Annihilus' throneworld; Reed searches for hardware that Annihilus stole from Four Freedoms Plaza, while Ben, Sue, and Johnny battle Annihilus; their combined skills bring them home, to learn that Paris has been overtaken by the Ruined.
name: Down & Out In The Negative Zone

description:
Spider-man has come to give a charity show in a circus. But it seems that he has been hypnotized by the Ringmaster. So is the rest of the audience. Except one man. Matt Murdock wonders what has happened to the crowd. He slips behind the arena and changes into Daredevil. He sees the Ringmaster and Spider-man. The Ringmaster tries to hypnotize him but fails. He orders Spider-man to kill Daredevil. Spider-man obeys Ringmaster's commands with jerky movements, long enough for Daredevil to separate Ringmaster from his hat. He uses the hat to bring Spider-man back to normal. He and Spider-man together tackle the other circus actors and bring them down. Daredevil slips away. Spider-man survives an attack from Ringmaster and knocks him out. Then he uses the hat to bring the audience back to normal.

Kraven the Hunter watches all of this from behind. He releases a giant gorilla and steps into the arena to tackle it. He speaks before the crowd that he is here to hunt Spider man.

Kraven speaks to Chameleon about Spider-man and hatches plans to bring him down.

J.Jonah Jameson tells Peter to get pictures of Kraven capturing Spider-man. That night, Spider-man runs into Kraven after taking down a bunch of goons. Kraven proves too much for Spider-man. Spider-man cannot defend himself and Kraven strikes him with a nerve venom. Then he leaves the scene.

The next day, Peter finds his hands shaking uncontrollably. He sees a picture of Kraven in the newspaper, then hunts for him on the internet. May Parker comes in and asks him to go out with Mary Jane someday.

Spider-man comes to Central Park and finds Kraven jogging. He chases him but falls into a net. A second Kraven comes out and puts two magnetic bands on his limbs. Spider-man struggles to keep them from bonding together. He attacks Kraven but finds that it is Chameleon wearing Kraven's mask. Spider-man renews his search and traps the real Kraven in a web. He delivers a mighty punch which shatters the magnetic bands. He leaves Kraven trussed up for the police to find him.

Superman guests in the incredibly angry, absurdly funny miniseries from the writer of NEVADA and the artists of Quantum & Woody! Al Bizarro tries to end his miserable, misbegotten life by jumping in front of a truck...and gets rescued by the Man of Steel himself! Seems poor Al can't do anything wrong...er, right! Plus, Lex Luthor tries to reclaim his suicidal property and the Guardian tries to keep Al from embarking on a life of crime in Suicide Slum.
name: Silicon Dreamer

description: In the not-too-distant future, Stacy idles away her life in a personal Hell, tailor-made for her by the Devil himself. Faces come and go, and judgment day is rapidly approaching. Her life is near its conclusion, and the Devil's cold grasp is now reaching for Stacy's only child--Christine Spar, the inheritor of Hunter Rose's ominous mantle.
name: [All Alone, with Grendel Cat]

description:
"No Man's Land" part 23 and "Fruit of the Earth" part 2, continued from BATMAN: SHADOW OF THE BAT #88. After battling to enter Robinson Park, Batman and Robin must fight Clayface to free the enslaved Poison Ivy and gain access to a Batcave buried deep within Ivy's paradise. Continued in DETECTIVE COMICS (1937-2011) #735.

Clayface had been holding Ivy, forcing her to grow food for him, and enslaving the children she'd been caring for. Robin began getting the children to safety; Batman began attempting to get Ivy free from the brick-like clay that held her. As Clayface returned, Robin set off explosives that freed Ivy. Huntress joined Pettit's group.
name: No Man's Land: Fruit of the Earth, Part Two

description: Batman gathers his forces in "Assembly," a self-contained story that represents a critical turning point in the battle to reclaim "No Man's Land," beginning with the revelation of Batgirl's true identity! The Dark Knight has alienated those who once trusted him with their lives ? Robin, Nightwing and Oracle among them. After unmasking the new Batgirl and replacing her with another mysterious heroine and summoning Azrael to his side, Batman must now regain his former allies' trust and co-ordinate their efforts if his plan to regain control of Gotham is to succeed.
name: Assembly

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description: The surviving members of the Justice Society of America unite to bid farewell to a fallen comrade, Wesley Dodds who is also known as the Sandman. While at the burial, Fate appears to inform the Society members that he was murdered just like Dodds. A group of mummies arise from the ground to gather Fate's weapons, but the JSA stop them. After the mummies are defeated, the Scarab appears with some answers.
name: Justice Be Done

description: Having journeyed to an alternate reality where they are forced to battle distorted versions of the original Avengers, the next generation of the Earth¹s Mightiest Heroes join with the Captain America! Can the young team stop the dastardly Doctor Doom? They better, or else the demented despot will extend his nightmarish empire across every plane of reality! Plus: American Dream finally gets her very own shield and the A-Next squad faces its first fatal casualty!
name: Crucible!

description:
In the previous issue, Spidergirl was zapped into the past while trying to prevent the villain Spyral from returning to his home dimension. As to what happened next was auful for her. She had to battle the original Spiderman and still failed to prove her innocence. She managed to sleep in the girls' lockers of Midtown High. And she got attacked by Jameson's new Spider-Slayer robot.

Now, May is leaping from rooftop to rooftop in order to evade the Spider-Slayers tentacles. She barely manages to duck out and get some distance when the machine suddenly stops.

Jameson, who is controlling the robot, observes Spidergirl. He thinks of her as Spiderman and says that he has got some wild ideas about costume selection.

May runs into the Human Torch on her way to the Parker Residence. The Human torch quickly realises that this Spider-person isn't the one he is familiar with and resorts to methods of containing her. Spidergirl manages to evade him and ducks into a nearby high-rise. She changes back to May Parker and heads for the Parker Residence. There she meets young Mary Jane, who would one day grow up to be her mom, and a few other girls. She tellsMary Jane that she and her mother share the same shopping tastes. With that, May takes her leave.

May is circling the building wher she first appeared with Spyral. But she is interrupted when Spiderman notices her and pulls her with him. May manages to outwit him but doesn't escape. Johnny Storm reappears on the scene. Now May has a hard time escaping two of the greatest heroes-her heroes! The most ironic part is that she can't prove her innocence. That is until a familiar green portal marks the arrival of Spyral. Spyral is waiting for her to go back with him into her proper timeline. She pleads to the two heroes to let her go. Johnny doesn't believe her but Spiderman interrupts him to help her. May thanks him and calls him "dad". With that, she disappears into the portal with Spyral. They appear in the proper timeline and May clobbers Spyral before he can make his getaway.

May comes home in a cheerful mood. She spots Mary Jane and invites her to go shopping together. Peter enters the scene and recieves a big hug from his daughter. They are both puzzled, while May whistles away to her room.
name: Slayers, Spiders and Torches-- Oh My!

description: It's Bloodstorm vs. Havok for the life of his son! The Goblin Queen's lust for power grows, and with the help of Reed Richards and a dimensional gateway, she may get whatever she desires! But before she begins, Madelyne wants her son at her side, and that means she has to steal him away from the protection of Havok and the X-Men. So who better to send against them than the former X-Man herself, the vampiric Bloodstorm!
name: And a Child Shall Lead Them

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: J2 takes on Shang Chi, Iron Fist, the Sons of the Tiger, the Cat, the White Tiger and even Howard the Duck in "The Master of Jug-Fu!" Lured into a martial arts tournament, Juggie faces some over-the-hill, but former all-time greats! But why have all these fighters come out of retirement? That's an answer only our surprise super-villain knows for sure! Plus: Wolverine insists that his daughter, Rina, the Wild Thing, join the Uncanny X-People! But Jubilee's test is a whole lot harder than taking the S.A.T.s!
name: The Master of Jug-Fu! / Gauntlet

description:
Enemies of the past return! A powerless Aquaman is forced to outwit his opponents.

Following his battle with Charybdis Aquaman searches for clues to find his way back to Atlantis now that he lacks his telepathy, stumbling across many United States military weapons on the ocean floor. He then finds Black Manta's sub near the bombs he's found. He then breaks into the sub which is filled with water and the crew murdered he then finds what he believes to be Manta dead only to find a note saying impostors will die. Aquaman then follows a group of fish carrying seaweed who pass it off to crabs onshore where he runs into Porm's killer Demon Gate who reveals he's been killing the animals who delivered his food, this causes Aquaman to decide to break the deal which he can no longer do without his telepathy so he returns to Manta's ship for his helmet so he can breathe underwater.

He is then attacked by Demon Gate who has linked with the helmet's weapons and summons Black Manta's ship. He then attacks Aquaman with the ship's weapons, but himself is attacked by Black Manta who cuts the helmets oxygen hose filling it with water as demon gate then drains the sub of water. However the ship is destroyed by Aquaman throwing the crate of bombs destroying the ship. Aquaman is then forced to let Black Manta go to save Demon Gate bringing him to a new island with more food and releasing the fish from their duty of caring for him.
name: Watery Graves

description:
Green Lantern must team up with the dubious duo of Booster Gold and Plastic Man to stop a secret organization from obtaining a mysterious package.

A mysterious package is accidentally delivered to Kyle's apartment, and its owner--surprisingly enough, a super-villain --- will do anything to get it back. It seems like your typical super-hero fun and games until Plastic Man is captured. Now GL and Booster may have to sacrifice the package's contents to save Plastic life!
name: The Package

description:
Hourman, Snapper Carr, and Bethany Lee are at the Tyler manor, where Snapper has convinced Hourman into taking some Miraclo. Hourman does, and starts going into hallucinatory fits. During them, he lives an overly-exaggerated version of the life of the first Hourman, Rex Tyler.
 
Hourman is living his predecessor’s life through surreal circumstances. Snapper Carr appears in the hallucination in a 1940’s zoot suit, trying to help guide him out of it. Meanwhile Hourman relives various events of the first Hourman’s life, including a fight with Dr. Togg and his Gambezis, Tyler’s early childhood, his time at college, his work at Bannermain Chemical, his adventures with the Justice Society, dating Wendi Harris and the birth of his son Rick, Rick taking the Hourman name, Rick’s battle with leukemia, and Tyler’s death at the hands of Extant.
 
Meanwhile, in the real world, Hourman is going on a rampage, destroying the Tyler manor. Snapper and Bethany try to lay low to avoid being hurt. Back at Snapper’s home, Amazo has returned.
 
In the hallucination, Hourman is experiencing what it means to be human through the hallucinations, realizing the love and hate he feels, as Tyler, for Wendi and Rick. Once his hour is up, Hourman awakens from his hallucination to find that he has destroyed a portion of the Tyler manor. In response, the JLA shows up; however, instead of the real JLA, we find that these are android versions of Superman, Wonder Woman, Green Lantern, Flash, and Plastic Man.
name: The Death of Hourman

deck: Supergirl battle Parasite in Paris. Part 2 of 2.
description: In the conclusion of a 2-part story, Supergirl battles the Parasite in the City of Lights! Unfortunately, it may be lights out for the Maid of Might in Paris, as the Parasite keeps trying to absorb her powers...and her life essence! Meanwhile, watching from a safe distance are the mysterious Mr. Carnivean and Lex Luthor, which can't mean good things for Supergirl!
name: For Those Who Came In Late...

description: A long-unseen character from THE SANDMAN returns for this special issue, guest-written by Peter Hogan (THE DREAMING) with art by original THE BOOKS OF MAGIC series artist Gary Amaro. When young mage Tim Hunter is kidnapped by mystically-inclined gangsters, he learns of an ancient power operating at the heart of London's underworld.
name: The Good Fella

description: Scarlett tries to convince Alex to join her and run away from New York. As tempting an offer as that may be, he is determined to find the elusive Lisseth and face his destiny. But to accomplish that, he must first find Joe, a difficult task in a city where a modern-day Inquisition is chasing away all the creatures of the night.
name: Memoria

description: Sam & Twitch are back on the force! And they have one hell of a case...
name: Udaku, Part 1

description: VERTIGO's new ongoing horror anthology offers three offbeat horror stories to darken your summer days and nightmares. In "Satanic," that well-known star-crossed ship on its maiden voyage goes down yet again in a horrific yarn based on a nightmare (written by Garth Ennis, with art by Kieron Dwyer); in "Night Terrors," a young boy awaits his primal fear in front of a ticking grandfather clock (written by John Rozum and illustrated by Kelley Jones); and in "A Walk In the Park," a stroke-ridden old woman is taken for a sadistic spin through Central Park by her homicidal nurse (written by Scott Cunningham and illustrated by Marcelo Frusin).
name: Night Terrors; A Walk in the Park; Satanic

description: The writer-artist team behind the acclaimed JONNY DOUBLE returns with a gripping new ongoing series, featuring painted covers by artist Dave Johnson ("The Justice Society Returns!"). Everyone talks about "getting away with murder," but what would you do if you were given irrefutable proof of the identity of the one that "done you wrong," the opportunity to kill them and the means to get away with it, scot-free? When former gangbanger Dizzy Cordova meets the mysterious Agent Graves, she is given the opportunity of a lifetime in the form of an attache case containing the proof, the gun, and the carte blanche immunity to exact revenge for the drive-by shootings that killed her family. Now she faces the hardest decision of her life in the form of a question that has no easy answer: If you could get away with murder, and your victim truly deserved it, what would you do?
name: 100 Bullets

description: From the minds that brought you DarkMinds comes the epic battle comic book fans have been waiting for! Three years ago, Dreamwave Productions envisioned a huge project involving literally dozens of characters and storylines. Characters and storylines which are all set in one place, Warlands, a fantasy world of myth and magic, inhabited by people of every mythical race imaginable, and threatened by an evil beyond comprehension. Dreamwave Productions proudly presents the first 12-issue story arc of Warlands. If you only buy one comic this summer, Warlands should be it! We guarantee that Warlands will be just as big a hit as DarkMinds, if not more so!
name: The Fall Of Shal Hazar

description: A guest-star packed final issue concludes the 3-part "Millennium Meteor." As Earth's mightiest heroes (Superman, Wonder Woman and members of the Titans and Young Justice) fall before the reality-altering power of Warp Child, it's up to Mitch Shelley, Vandal Savage and the Immortal Man to track down the monster. Can they succeed where the others have failed? More important, can these mortal enemies work together long enough to defeat a common foe?
name: The End of the Earth

description: No Man's Land.
name: Inside Job

description: Inque has become the slave of a mad scientist whom she needs to stay alive.
name: Permanet Inque Stains

description: Robin and Nightwing team up to answer Batman's call to arms and rescue Gotham from its state as a "No Man's Land!" Using a treacherous, long-abandoned subterranean pathway to enter Gotham, Tim and Dick must defeat the tag-team of Gearhead and Tommy Mangles if they want to make it through. Meanwhile, a certain Ratcatcher is waiting in the wings.
name: Way Dark

description:
The JLA guest-stars in the senses-shattering conclusion to "Justice For All." For months, J'onn has been plagued by the ruthless machinations of Malefic. Now, pushed to the edge of his endurance, the Martian Manhunter and his allies from the JLA battle J'onn's brother in one of the most astonishing showdowns of the year!

Although Malefic is largely successful in pitting the Justice League of America against each other through his shape-shifting manipulations, his one true threat has returned in the form of J'onn J'onzz - the Martian Manhunter. As a result from absorbing mass from the Earth, J'onn is unable to control his shape-shifting and remains in his Manhunter form while battling his physically superior twin brother. The two battle aboard the flying city of Z'onn Z'orr, and only one will survive.
name: The Burning Grave

description: The three acrobats escaped from the three goons. Nightwing let the mooks run back to Blockbuster (who learned that he needed a heart transplant), while Double Dare escaped. Batman called Nightwing back to Gotham.
name: Sister Act

description: Batman is the enemy...and Catwoman is the Champion of Justice?  That's how it is in THIS mirror-image universe, where the names and faces only seem familiar...
name: Part 1: Guardian of Gotham

description: Batman, Robin and Batgirl investigate a series of brazen bank robberies committed by Bane, only to find out that the villain has set himself up as a modern day Robin Hood to Gotham City's downtrodden.
name: Cash 'n the Hood

description: First full Appearance of Valeria Richards (as an adult), she first appeared in a cameo in Fantastic Four vol. 3 no. 15
name: "...Itza Been Ruined!"

description:
Overview

A mysterious robbery in an ancient English mansion sets Hellboy and Abe Sapien on the trail of a saint, a warlock, a demon, an arch duke of Hell, and a gun-wielding monkey. The crown of the Beast of the Apocalypse becomes the main prize in a tale perfectly balancing action and occult suspense. Also this issue: Lobster Johnson, Mignola's new 1930s costumed adventurer, makes his debut in "The Killer in My Skull," written by Mignola, penciled by Matt Smith, and inked by Ryan Sook.
name: Box Full of Evil; The Killer in My Skull

first_appearance_teams.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

team_credits.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

description: We've seen connections made between Norman Osborn and several Spidey villains, including the Vulture and Sandman. What other mysteries of Norman will we delve into for the first time? And as we climb inside the bewitched brain of the Green Goblin, we also get to watch Spider-Man foul up his big chance to make a positive impact on the public! Hey, it could only happen to our wonky web-head!
name: Goblin Redux

description:
In order to prove herself to Batman, Batgirl has secures a local gas station and awaits for Batman to arrive for its retrieval. However, a rival gang destroys the station with a rocket launcher upon discovery that the station is empty.

Batgirl lashes out against the gang in anger and is on the verge of killing a gang member when the owner of the gas station convinces her not to. As a reward he unveils a secret stash of gasoline to power the hospital's generators.
name: I Cover the Waterfront

description: Batman battles Mr. Freeze for a vital source of power in "No Man's Land!" Freeze is attempting to expand his range of operations from the Gotham power plant he controls through Chinatown and beyond to push the city further into anarchy. But the Dark Knight has other plans, resulting in an action-packed, explosive confrontation.
name: NML: Power Play

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description: In an extra-sized final issue, Superman must save Lois's soul from the depths of hell in the face of DAY OF JUDGMENT! In "The Heart of Hell," Silver Banshee has taken Lois Lane's soul deep into the bowels of Hell, and the Man of Steel must confront all sorts of personal hells (courtesy of Neron) in order to save her.
name: Last Rites!

description: Scarab asks the Justice Society of America to help find the next person to become Doctor Fate. Scarab was able to determine, thanks to Wesley Dodds (aka the original Sandman), that there are three potential babies that could become the next Dr. Fate. The Society splits up to investigate and find themselves being attacked by the Egyptian zombies from Wesley Dodds' funeral. The last team, led by Wildcat, find the baby they were meant to find being held by a new Hawkgirl. Hawkgirl explains her part in the events unfolding when they are all attacked by Mordru, the Dark Lord.
name: The Wheel Of Life

description: This lethal last issue introduces the Revengers: Red Queen, Big Man, Killerwatt, Ion Man and Sabreclaw! Returning from their most recent battle with three less members, the team is confronted by an all-new super-team that has only one desire: to crush the surviving Avengers! All the events from the first 12 issues lead to this issue!
name: The End of the Avengers!

description: Spider-Girl discovers she has a new power, one that Spider-Man never had! May Parker¹s relationship with Darkdevil is turned upside down when Spider-Girl discovers that her tough-love mentor has a deadly and secret agenda! Torn between her sense of responsibility and her loyalty, our stunning web-slinger must make a pivotal choice!
name: Duel With Darkdevil

description: As we learn the true origin of the Goblin Queen, Havok and the heroes rally their forces, and they're joined by their surprise ally, the benevolent ruler of Europe, Victor Von Doom! If you've been following this book since issue #1, you know it's all been headed toward this final showdown, but like THOR #12, this issue also includes explosive events which will spin MUTANT X in startling new directions!
name: Once Upon a Time

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: In his last issue, J2 finally finds the original Juggernaut! With the aid of Doc Magus, Dr. Stranger, the Hulk and Sub-Mariner, Zane Yama reunites with his father! But is our young hero prepared to pay the price and make the awful sacrifice that¹s needed to bring his dad back home?! What will DeFalco and company do to Juggie in his last issue? Hey, this is MC2 anything is possible!
name: Deadly Reunion!

description:
With Gindola's oil being pumped into the ocean, toxins are sickening civilians. Aquaman must stop the leak and figure out Gindola's real plan.

A frustrated Aquaman furiously questions Vulko over his telling him that his mother was dead which Vulko sticks by as confused as all the others with Aquaman confused if the disfigured woman is who she claims to be. Indigo then arrives and shows Aquaman the amount of people being hurt by the effect Gindola's oil, while Garth and Dolphin continue to plan for their wedding. While Blubber,Sheeva and Lagoon Boy set out to build a television set.meanwhile Aquaman sets out to question Atlan over his not using his magic to heal his mother only to learn it's still gone causing him to age rapidly.

While the Gindola provider reveals to be pumping the toxin into the water in hopes of causing a riot which will lead to Aquaman and the others death in the hopes of Atlanna becoming the new king. Aquaman then returns to the aquacave to gather the parts of the destroyed machine to give him and Atlan their powers back but are met by looters and a villain named the Eel.He then defeats him and returns to the palace gathering Garth and Indigo and heading to battle the Kingfish following his theft of the Gindola fish. Aquaman then defeats Kingfish as Mera arrives becoming jealous, with Atlan arriving shortly after to reveal Indigo is in fact Arthur's sister.
name: Drugs of Choice

description: Plastic Man and Booster Gold guest-star in the conclusion of a 2-part story written by Dan Jurgens! Things get serious as Plastic Man is being tortured by the Supplier, a villain who's been behind-the-scenes in the DCU for quite some time. Green Lantern and Booster Gold have to save Plas and find out the Supplier's shocking secret.
name: Machinations, Misconceptions, and Revelations!

description:
Following his destruction of Rex Tyler’s estate last issue, Hourman has been attacked by the JLAndroids. Hourman has used his time powers to determine that these are not androids of the JLA, but rather the JLA has been transformed into androids. Hourman tries to outrun these android teammates at first, but finds that the android JLA are just as formidable as their human counterparts.
 
Hourman surrenders, but then finds that his crime for damaging the Tyler manor is to me disassembled. He again puts up a fight, when Amazo arrives. The android Justice League split their forces to deal with Hourman and Amazo, and Hourman finds that, without teamwork, they do not function nearly as well as they should. Amazo defeats the android JLA easily, and reveals that he is behind the JLA’s fate.
 
Amazo takes Hourman to a local hospital’s maternity ward. He asks Hourman to punch him, and Hourman accepts his request. After Hourman punches him, Amazo reveals that he is bleeding. Amazo has discovered a way to absorb more than just super-powers: he can now absorb someone’s humanity. He demonstrates by absorbing the humanity of two infants, turning them into androids as well. Hourman tries to attack, but this new Amazo is too much for him. Amazo leaves, with the intention of finally destroying the Justice League.
 
Hourman returns to Snapper Carr and Bethany, where the cops try to arrest him for the damage done at the Tyler manor. Hourman avoids arrest, and takes Snapper with him to help defeat Amazo. However, before they could get too far, Amazo arrives and steals Snapper’s humanity, transforming Snapper into an android as well.
name: The JLAndroids

description: Part 2 of a 4-part crossover pitting Young Justice and Supergirl against the disco menace of Dante's Inferno! A few issues back, Supergirl was almost run down by Young Justice. Now she gets the opportunity to give 'em a good talking to, that is, if she can stop the team when they're under the mental control of Dante and his mind-controlling winged monkeys!
name: Heck's Angels, Part 2: Justice Delayed

description:
Overview

The greatest heroes of the Marvel Universe go to war, with each other, in this all-new super slugfest! From deep space comes the Coiterie, a group of intergalactic samaritans who come to Earth seeking its most powerful champion, through all-out combat! But what could possibly make our heroes compete against one another? How about this: the victor receives a miraculous wish of their choice! In other words, the winner could once and for all save mankind! But as Wolverine, Spider-Man, the Thing, Rogue, Thor, Hulk and a legion of heroes are culled from the Avengers, Fantastic Four and the X-Men, the participants begin to wonder: could their alien hosts really have a more sinister agenda?! They better figure it out soon,before they take each other out!

Plus: This series will bring two new heroes to the Marvel Universe (hint: check out FANTASTIC FOUR #17 & #18)! These brutal bouts are brought to you by writer Chris Claremont (FANTASTIC FOUR), penciler Oscar Jimenez (WOLVERINE: BLACK RIO) and inker Eduardo Alpuente.
name: The Gathering

description: Saint George visits the Templar Knights and tries to convince them to leave New York without a fight. But they're out for blood and make him confront his most dire nightmare: The Dragon. Also, Alex finds Ekimus, with whom he finally meets the eerie Lisseth.
name: Cantus Excio
